description.narrative: The development objective is to increase the efficiency, effectiveness and accountability of the CCC in order to: (i) promote internationally acceptable practices for expeditious processing of international trade flows, so as to further integrate the country into the world economy and improve the investment climate and competitiveness, (ii) improve taxpayer compliance with the Customs Code and thereby increase revenue collection, (iii) and support transparency of customs operations in order to reduce the potential for corruption and increase predictability for traders. The project will facilitate Kazakhstan#s accession to the WTO, as well as post-accession support.

baseline.value: Currently additional revenue generated as a result of post clerance control is 2%

target.value: Additional revenue generated as a result of post clearance control becomes 25%

comment.narrative: Under implementation. Data will be available in 2015.

title.narrative: Reduction in percentage of physical inspections of import declarations by Customs.

comment.narrative: Annual indicator. he data for 2014 will be available in Jan 2015.The indicator has shown huge improvement from baseline. Alreadyreached target level.

title.narrative: Integrated Tariff Automated System is developed and made operational and incorporates all other agency requirements.

target.value: Integrated Tariff Automated System is developed and made operational and incorporates 100% of all other agency requirements.

comment.narrative: Integrated tariff system contract is being implemented

title.narrative: Comprehensive training strategy, curriculum, and distance learning systems are developed and used for continuous professional development of CCC staff

target.value: Distance learning is used for continuous professional development by atleast 20% of customs staff.

title.narrative: New integrated IT system is available by the end of 2010, piloted by end of 2011, and is fully operational by end of 2012

target.value: New integrated IT system is fully operational

comment.narrative: The software development is under implementation. The BD for hardware is submitted.

title.narrative: Improved perception of traders and other stakeholders regarding the frequency of unofficial payments to customs officials as measured by periodic surveys

baseline.value: Baseline survey on client perception to be conducted on project initiation

title.narrative: Reduction in average customs processing time at the border posts (based on client surveys) by end of the Project

comment.narrative: Significant improvement in clearance time from 1.3 days to 13.9 hours

title.narrative: Number of documents required for border/customs clearance for imports

comment.narrative: Significant improvement well beyond the target value enshrined in the Customs Code.

title.narrative: Increase in ratio of total revenue collected by customs to number of customs staff.

comment.narrative: Annual indicator. The data for 2014 will be available in Jan 2015. The baseline was calculated prior to Kazakhstan’s participationin the Customs Union. Using 2011 asa new base we see performance has improved from 204% to 235% in 2013.
